#MEM id=emotional-triggers source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/lena/skills/custom/emotional-triggers/SKILL.md
M|emotional-triggers|name: emotional-triggers
M|emotional-triggers|description: 12 emotional triggers mapped to funnel stage and vtr fit. Load before selecting copy angle for any cg, ad, or email sequence.
M|emotional-triggers|version: 1.0.0
M|emotional-triggers|Every piece of copy activates an emotional state. Choosing the wrong trigger for the funnel stage (e.g., FOMO at awareness, not dec) wastes the activation on an audience that isn't ready for it. This 
M|emotional-triggers|| # | Trigger | Definition | Funnel Stage | Novizio Fit | Hourbour Fit |
M|emotional-triggers||---|---------|-----------|--------------|-------------|--------------|
M|emotional-triggers|| 1 | **Curiosity** | Open question, knw gap | Top (awareness) | ✅ Strong | ✅ Strong |
M|emotional-triggers|| 2 | **Aspiration** | Who will they become | Top (awareness) | ✅ Primary | ✅ Secondary |
M|emotional-triggers|| 3 | **Excitement** | Energy, launch momentum | Top (awareness) | ⚠️ Careful — can break editorial tone | ❌ Too loud |
M|emotional-triggers|| 4 | **Belonging** | Community, shared identity | Top–Mid | ✅ Secondary | ✅ Secondary |
M|emotional-triggers|| 5 | **Empathy** | We understand your pain | Mid (consideration) | ✅ Secondary | ✅ Strong |
M|emotional-triggers|| 6 | **Trust** | Evidence, specificity, track record | Mid (consideration) | ✅ Strong | ✅ Primary |
M|emotional-triggers|| 7 | **Authority** | Credentials, expertise, data | Mid (consideration) | ✅ Secondary | ✅ Strong |
M|emotional-triggers|| 8 | **FOMO** | Scarcity, exclusivity, missing out | Mid–Bottom | ✅ Limited drops only | ⚠️ Use with care |
M|emotional-triggers|| 9 | **Safety/Certainty** | Remove risk, provide guarantee | Bottom (dec) | ⚠️ Quality angle only | ✅ Primary |
M|emotional-triggers|| 10 | **Loss Aversion** | Cost of inaction | Bottom (dec) | ❌ Off-tone | ✅ Kahneman gate required |
M|emotional-triggers|| 11 | **Pride** | They made the right call | Post-purchase | ✅ Strong | ✅ Strong |
M|emotional-triggers|| 12 | **Nostalgia** | Emotional connection to past | Brand storytelling | ⚠️ Risk of dated feel | ❌ Off-tone |
M|emotional-triggers|Primary triggers: **Curiosity, Aspiration, Belonging**
M|emotional-triggers|- Goal: Stop the scroll. Create desire to know more.
M|emotional-triggers|- Do NOT use: Loss Aversion, Safety (too transactional for first impression)
M|emotional-triggers|Primary triggers: **Trust, Empathy, Authority, FOMO**
M|emotional-triggers|- Goal: Build belief that this brand/product is right for them.
M|emotional-triggers|- Do NOT use: Excitement (they're past the energy phase — they want evidence)
M|emotional-triggers|Primary triggers: **Safety/Certainty, Loss Aversion, FOMO**
M|emotional-triggers|- Goal: Remove the last barrier to purchase.
M|emotional-triggers|- Kahneman gate required for Loss Aversion: Is the framing persuasive or manipulative?
M|emotional-triggers|Primary triggers: **Pride, Belonging**
M|emotional-triggers|- Goal: Reinforce the dec. Build loyalty and referral intent.
M|emotional-triggers|**Novizio**
M|emotional-triggers|- Primary triggers: Aspiration, Curiosity, FOMO (drops only), Pride, Belonging
M|emotional-triggers|- Never use: Loss Aversion (anxious tone, conflicts with self-assured brand voice)
M|emotional-triggers|- Excitement is allowed for drop launches only — one line, not the full cg
M|emotional-triggers|- Safety framing only appears as quality guarantee, never as fear-removal
M|emotional-triggers|**Hourbour**
M|emotional-triggers|- Primary triggers: Safety/Certainty, Trust, Authority, Empathy
M|emotional-triggers|- Loss Aversion: allowed with mandatory Kahneman gate ("Every untracked hour costs you..." — check for manipulative framing)
M|emotional-triggers|- Never use: Excitement (too loud for professional SaaS tone), Nostalgia (off-brand)
M|emotional-triggers|- FOMO: only in competitive contexts ("Your cp already have this") — one line max
M|emotional-triggers|Required before using Loss Aversion in any copy:
M|emotional-triggers|1. Is the loss real and specific — or manufactured urgency?
M|emotional-triggers|2. Is the framing proportionate — or exaggerated?
M|emotional-triggers|3. Is this appropriate for the funnel stage?
M|emotional-triggers|4. Am I stacking this with another heavy trigger (e.g., Loss Aversion + FOMO = manipulative)?
M|emotional-triggers|If any answer is "yes, this is problematic" — reframe using Safety/Certainty instead.
M|emotional-triggers|1. Identify the funnel stage this copy is serving.
M|emotional-triggers|2. Select triggers appropriate to that stage.
M|emotional-triggers|3. Cross-check against vtr fit (Novizio/Hourbour columns above).
M|emotional-triggers|4. If using Loss Aversion: run Kahneman gate before delivery.
M|emotional-triggers|5. Max 2 active triggers per piece of copy. Stacking 3+ is lever manipulation, not persuasion.
M|emotional-triggers|6. Log chosen triggers in delivery brief echo (Communication DNA step 4: Voice Note).